This is my favorite Starbucks in town in terms of layout, atmosphere, and design. The service however is inexcusable and probably the worst I have experienced. The employees aren't being trained for efficiency and are always slow-moving and seem to do tasks in odd orders. I notice that when making drinks they won't set them out as they are finished, but instead hoard a line of finished drinks on the back bar until they finish everything and then move them all to the counter. WHY?! It's frustrating to stand at the bar waiting when you know your drink is ready, but nobody is handing it over. Often the employees are swinging a towel around laughing and chatting (and not working). I ordered an ice coffee (black... easy) and then ordered a refill of the same thing an hour later. The first time my coffee was poured, but sat on the back counter for over 5 minutes while the barista finished other drinks. Eventually the manager came over and asked what I was waiting for and I pointed at my finished drink and said I was merely waiting for my drink to be within arms reach. Absurd. When I got my refill, and I remind you it is simply dispensing pre-made coffee and adding ice (a 15 second effort), my cup sat empty on the bar while three employees laughed and talked. The employee responsible for making my drink decided to take this opportunity to very slowly show another employee how to make a shaken tea. Why wouldn't that employee just pour the 15 second coffee and get me on my way before starting this process? I checked the time on my sticker to see how long I waited and it was 8 minutes and 15 seconds. For an iced coffee! and no it wasn't because the store was busy. The employees are just slow and have no multi-tasking or time-management skills. Having been to probably 80 different Starbucks stores hundreds of times over the last 15 years I can't believe how frustrating it is to experience a store that runs as poorly as this one all without apology. Eight minutes doesn't sound like a long time, but when you are just standing, silently staring at your drink and not being able to take it, it feels like an eternity. This Starbucks makes me wish I could just walk around the counter, pick up the cup, pour coffee to the line, add ice, and walk out. It's not hard. As I sit here I'm watching customers with grumpy faces stand with their hands on their hips rolling their eyes at the employees doing anything other than work.
